    <div class="legal-card">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tighter mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-sm opacity-40 mb-10 italic">Last updated: February 2026</p>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h2 class="!border-l-0 !pl-0 !mb-4 text-xl">1. Our Philosophy: Privacy by Design</h2>
                <p class="!mb-0 !opacity-100">Shurp is built on one principle: we collect only what’s necessary — and
                    nothing more.</p>
                <p class="!mb-0 !opacity-100 font-medium">Your privacy isn’t a feature. It’s part of the architecture.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>2. Who is the Data Controller?</h2>
            <p>The personal data controller is:</p>
            <p><strong class="text-[#1F2933] font-bold">SIA Shurp</strong><br>
                Reg. No. LV40203709369<br>
                Address: Briežu iela 9, Lapsas, LV-2107, Latvia<br>
                Email for privacy inquiries: <span id="safe-email-p2"></span>
            </p>
            <p>We process personal data in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and Latvian
                legislation.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>3. What Data Do We Process?</h2>

            <p class="font-bold text-[#1F2933] !opacity-100 mb-2">Identity Data</p>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>Name</li>
                <li>Phone number</li>
                <li>Profile photo (if added)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm italic">Required so users know who they're riding with.</p>

            <p class="font-bold text-[#1F2933] !opacity-100 mb-2 mt-6">Verification Data</p>
            <p class="text-sm">If you verify your identity (e.g., as a driver through CSDD):</p>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>we do not store your personal document numbers,</li>
                <li>we only save an encrypted verification status.</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="font-bold text-[#1F2933] !opacity-100 mb-2 mt-6">Location Data (GPS)</p>
            <p class="text-sm">To find fellow travelers on the same route, we need:</p>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>origin and destination information</li>
                <li>route data</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm">Precise coordinates are processed only as long as necessary for trip facilitation. Shurp
                does not perform continuous or background location tracking.</p>

            <p class="font-bold text-[#1F2933] !opacity-100 mb-2 mt-6">Communication Data</p>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>Chat messages between users</li>
                <li>Technical communication with support</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="font-bold text-[#1F2933] !opacity-100 mb-2 mt-6">Technical Data</p>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>Device type</li>
                <li>App version</li>
                <li>Access time</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm italic">This data is used only for system security and stability.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>4. How Do We Protect Your Location?</h2>
            <p>We've intentionally built multiple layers of protection.</p>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li><strong>Location Anonymization:</strong> We don't use your exact address in search processes.</li>
                <li><strong>Dynamic Offset:</strong> Your route is processed in anonymized regions, ensuring no one can
                    trace your exact trip starting point.</li>
                <li><strong>Progressive Access:</strong> The exact meeting point becomes visible only after trip
                    confirmation.</li>
                <li><strong>Private Routes:</strong> Your regular routes ("Magic Button") are not publicly visible until
                    you confirm a trip.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>5. Legal Basis for Data Processing</h2>
            <p>We process data based on:</p>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>Contract performance (organizing trips between users)</li>
                <li>Legal obligation compliance</li>
                <li>Legitimate interests (platform security)</li>
                <li>User consent (e.g., location access)</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>6. How Long Do We Store Data?</h2>
            <p>We don't like digital dust.</p>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>Detailed trip coordinates are anonymized after 30 days.</li>
                <li>Chat history is deleted 30 days after the trip ends.</li>
                <li>Technical logs are stored for limited periods for security purposes.</li>
                <li>If you delete your account, personal data is permanently removed from active systems.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>7. Data Sharing with Third Parties</h2>
            <p>We don't sell your personal data to advertisers.</p>
            <p>Advertising content is served based on non-identifiable criteria (general route or region) without
                disclosing your identity. This is conducted in accordance with GDPR principles.</p>
            <p>Data may be shared between driver and passenger, or with technical service providers (DPA agreements in
                place).</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>8. Security</h2>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>Data is encrypted during transmission and storage.</li>
                <li>Sensitive information is not stored in plain text.</li>
                <li>Data access is restricted and auditable.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>Under GDPR, you have the right to access, correct, or delete your data, and to restrict or object to
                processing.</p>
            <p>Requests can be submitted through the app, or by writing to: <span id="safe-email-p9"></span></p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>If we make significant changes, we will notify you in the app or on the website.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <div class="legal-footer-box">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">Data Controller</p>
                        <p class="font-bold">SIA Shurp</p>
                        <p class="text-sm opacity-60">Reg. No. LV40203709369</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">Legal Address</p>
                        <p class="text-sm">Briežu iela 9, Lapsas, LV-2107, Latvia</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pt-4 border-t border-[#E2E8F0] md:col-span-2">
                        <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">DSA Contact Point</p>
                        <span id="safe-email-footer"></span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <div class="pt-8 text-center">
            <a href="./"
                class="text-[#125E8A] font-bold hover:opacity-80 transition underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4">Back
                to Homepage</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <footer class="py-12 px-8 bg-[#125E8A] text-center text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest">
        <p class="text-white/70">&copy; 2026 SHURP. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
        const setupEmail = (id) => {
            const email = "legal" + "@" + "shurp.lv";
            const el = document.getElementById(id);
            if (el) el.innerHTML = `<a href="mailto:${email}" class="text-[#125E8A] hover:underline font-bold">${email}</a>`;
        };
        setupEmail("safe-email-p2");
        setupEmail("safe-email-p9");
        setupEmail("safe-email-footer");
    </script>
</body>

